stylometry: The coefficient of correlation is "R squared" and is the reliability of the data. The ranges from -1 to +1. An example of a strong negative correlation is -.98. An example of a strong positive correlation is .89. A strong negative correlation can be seen with the sale of bathing suits during the christmas season. A strong positive correlation can be seen in christmas trees in mid and end december. No correlation (close to 0) would occur when an event is not effected by another, example; the amount of rain fall effecting computer sales.
